The paper proposes a method for detecting overlapping community structures in complex networks. This topic falls under the scope of several arXiv CS sub-categories, including social and information networks (cs.SI), machine learning (cs.LG), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses experiments on both synthetic and real-world networks, which could potentially place it in the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SE) or databases (cs.DB). However, given the focus on community detection and machine learning techniques, we believe that cs.SI and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.SD, cs.DS, and cs.SY.
